paragraph
 Asymptote is a descriptive vector graphics language — developed by Andy Hammerlindl, John C. Bowman (University of Alberta), and Tom Prince — which provides a natural coordinate-based framework for technical drawing. Asymptote runs on all major platforms (Unix, Mac OS, Microsoft Windows). <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asymptote_(vector_graphics_language)">Read more on Wikipedia...</a>

